      {
        "path": "README.md",
        "heading": "How to Run It Locally",
        "body": "The app reads its game data (players, teams, ratings) from a **local Supabase Postgres** —\nwithout it the client throws on boot and the UI renders empty. First-time setup is the full\nchain below, not just `install` + `dev`.\n\n**No Supabase account needed.** Everything runs locally — `supabase start` spins up the whole\nstack on your machine, and the player/team data ships as committed CSVs in `supabase/seed/`.\nThe keys you'll see are Supabase's universal local demo keys (the same on every machine).",
        "fenced_blocks": [
          "pnpm install",
          "pnpm supabase:start",
          "pnpm db:reset",
          "pnpm seed",
          "pnpm dev"
        ]
      }
